doornail
Ars Scholae Palatinae
Registered: Aug 26, 2003Posts: 1105
Posted: Tue Aug 21, 2007 12:32 pm
I was online when it happened and it was hilarious. From what I understand, there was an encounter in Zul'Gurub where players would get infected with this short duration disease that did wicked damage and was highly contagious to any other players standing too close. The idea was the infected player would run away to prevent the deaths of his raiding buddies.The thing was pets could catch it too and die. When the player re-summoned the pet it would still have the disease. It was never meant to leave Zul'Gurub but, due to the pet bug, it spread life wildfire in whatever area the pet was re-summoned.There were corpses all over the main cities. People dropping dead in waves, respawning, and catching it again.I question the value as a 'pandemic simulation' though. It wasn't a heroic battle against an encroaching plague. It was more like, "I think I'll go to the bank and WTF?! I'm dead?" There's only so much you can extrapolate from the cartoony magic of a bugged MMORPG.
