Posted: Tue Aug 21, 2007 4:01 pm
I think that there are a lot of interesting possibilities with this. Primarily around other non-lethal but annoying effects of diseases. Like a social disease that is carried by some enemies, and once transmitted to a character it is only transmitted through contact with other characters (like trading). The effects or presence of the disease does not appear for say one hour and once it manifests it starts lowering stats, lessoning the effects of healing items or spells. The character can still play, but is just plain weaker.The more interesting diseases would be hard to simulate in a game without seriously angering gamers. Like Herpes, something that is incurable and has a huge social prejudice against it... It will be interesting to see what the developers of WoW come up with.
