Call me cynical but this sounds like nothing more than cheap CV-padding for junior professors and post-docs desperately seeking that elusive tenure-track dream job (not to mention a juicy NIH grant in the meantime).Yes, these things very well could be simulated in a realistic/useful manner, but WoW is not the vehicle for doing it. As the Penny Arcade strip referenced above not-so-subtly alludes, people tend to be very much not themselves on the 'net -- let's face it, that's the very point of RPG games, ain't it?.
