I, too, hovered over the 'links'. Bravo sir, bravo.Also, the Zul'Gurub debuff wasn't the only one that was able to be 'brought out' so to speak. I was never able to recreate this event, but I had it happen to me once. Basically, in the Upper Blackrock Spire instance, a hunter is typically called upon to 'kite' the last boss out of the room, so the other group members can kill the adds much easier. That particular boss doles out a nasty debuff called 'conflaguration', which does a lot of damage over a short amount of time, and affects others in range of the person affected. I had kited that boss, and during the fight my pet had beeen hit with conflag, typically something that would kill him in a quick hurry. But, I had just gotten out of 'pet range' and my pet despawned with the debuff. I didn't think anything of it until later, when I was sitting at the auction house, and called him out for some reason or another, and there he was, on fire, running around all crazy like. I do believe I killed at least 5 alts before he bit it, almost killing myself in the process. I found it terribly amusing, but it wasn't something easy to reproduce.
