Posted: Wed Aug 22, 2007 5:04 pm
Great idea, except:- "Death" in game is not the same as death in real life.- The average player in a battleground in WoW dies what? ten, twenty times in half an hour?- Its very unlikelly to have a plague in the real world where all the victims are unaware that they are infected.- The infected players feel no physical disconfort from the disease. There is no way you can come close to an even remotely accurate model of an epidemic under these conditions. As a player though, it would be great to see some epidemics running around. But only for the fun factor, since i don't believe there's any real use for WoW by "epidemiology researchers".EDIT: Also... invisible plagues = more work on the server = slower game.
